{Mrs de Newtown is retiring from {teaching this year.}
I brought my family up before I started teaching. I used to teach in a small room but now they have turned it into a T.V. room. They used to have a black and white T.V. but now the P.T.A. have bought a colour T.V. The office used to be a boys' cloakroom but they turned it into an office because Mr Kent asked them to.
If you have a favourite pupil you are a bad teacher. I have 24 pupils in my class, 14 boys and 10 girls. I come at 8.00 a.m. and I go home at 3.30 p.m.
